>How to make both sides equivalent!!
>
>[Thoughts]
>I've substituted the terms for Tan 2A and multiplied the other Tan A 
>which equals 
>2tanA (tanA)
>-----
>1-tan^2 A
>
>or 2Tan^2 A
>  ---------
>   1-Tan^2 A
>
>But where to go from here??
>
>Please help, thank you.

Hi Jason,

Usually, the place to start is by replacing tan, cot, sec, and csc
with equivalents using just sin and cos.  Then you look for
opportunities to replace (sin^2 + cos^2) with 1, or opportunities to
cancel out sines and cosines. 

Try that, and let me know what you get. 

- Doctor Ian, The Math Forum
